title: Breeding Bird Colonies, Central/Northern California Coast
name: Breeding Bird Colonies, Central/Northern California Coast
description:
Colonies is a shapefile of breeding colony locations for 17 marine bird species that occur along the northern/central California coast; area extending approximately from Point Arena, south to Point Sal. Data on these marine bird colonies (colony latitude/longitude coordinates, numbers of breeding birds per species) were derived primarily from 'Breeding Populations of Seabirds in California, 1989-1991'.
Colonies shapefile was created as part of a study to assess marine bird use of coastal California waters within and adjacent to the Monterey Bay, Gulf of the Farallones, and Cordell Bank National Marine Sanctuaries. This file was produced for graphic/map display of the breeding colonies for 17 marine bird species.
Colonies shapefile was created as part of a biogeographic assessment of marine resources off northern and central California, for the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration's Ocean Service.
